  "text": "Generation of 4-hydroxytamoxifen liposomes. We generated hydrophobic liposomal vesicles [CITATION_1] and produced 4-hydroxytamoxifen liposomes (LiTMX) (Fig. 1a ). Liposomes showed stability after 100 nm and 200 nm extrusion, with expected hydrodynamic diameters relative to the starting nanoparticle size, on dynamic light scattering (DLS) analysis ( Fig. 1b ). LiTMX showed reliable uptake of multiple concentrations of 4-hydroxytamoxifen and stability measured at 12 weeks post-production ( Fig. 1c) .",
